===Usage note===
As the two terms ''duct tape'' and ''[[duck tape]]'' are pronounced practically identically except in careful speech, either may be used.  Note, however, that ''Duck&reg; tape'' is a registered trade mark.

===Noun===
'''[[duct]] [[tape]]''' ''(uncountable)''

# A generally gray waterproof [[tape]] used for many purposes, and possessing nearly mythic status in American culture. It is no longer used for constructing duct-work, as building codes require a special heat-proof tape and the technology of ductwork has moved on.
#: ''Son, it’s time you learned to use the family duct tape.''
#also, ductology, the study of duct tape, ductism, the beleif that duct tape is supreme to all, and duct theory, the theory that duct tape holds the universe together.
#Ductovsky theory-The theory that not all duct tape is created equal
#General Ductivity-If two peices of duct tape are stuck together, sticky side to sticky side, it is no longer sticky.
#Special Ductiviity-An exception to General Ductivity, if the tape is a low quality brand they can be pulled apart.

===Verb===
'''to duct tape'''{{transitive}}
#to use duct tape in order to [[tape]] one object to another

